HEADWORD: Inexhausted
<hw>In`ex*haust"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>exhausted</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>inexhaustus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not exhausted; not emptied; not
spent; not having lost all strength or resources; unexhausted.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

